error.signature: An error occurred (ParameterNotFound) when calling the GetParameter operation

verdict.summary: SSM Parameter Store key does not exist or the name is wrong.

dead_ends.action: Creating the parameter with an empty value
dead_ends.why_fails: Empty values cause application errors downstream

dead_ends.action: Hardcoding the value instead of using Parameter Store
dead_ends.why_fails: Loses the benefits of centralized config management

workarounds.action: Verify the parameter name and path: aws ssm get-parameter --name '/myapp/config'
workarounds.how: Parameter names are case-sensitive and path-based

workarounds.action: Check the region â€” Parameter Store is regional; the parameter may exist in a different region
workarounds.how: Use --region flag or AWS_DEFAULT_REGION env var to specify
